---
import AIPointer from "./AIPointer.astro";
---

<div
  class="dark:bg-neutral-900 bg-gray-200 rounded-3xl font-medium text-lg z-0"
>
  <div class="flex justify-between py-4 px-6">
    <div class="flex items-center space-x-4">
      <div class="space-y-2">
        <div class="h-[3px] w-8 bg-neutral-200"></div>
        <div class="h-[3px] w-8 bg-neutral-200"></div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <span class="text-neutral-500">10-seo-tips</span>
        <span class="text-neutral-700 font-normal">â€” saved</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="flex items-center">
      <div class="text-gray-200">Publish</div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="bg-neutral-800 rounded-xl px-8 py-16">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-2xl">
      <div class="font-bold text-3xl mb-8 dark:text-gray-200 text-gray-700">
        10 SEO Tips
      </div>
      <div class="dark:text-gray-400 font-normal text-gray-600 space-y-8">
        <p>Here is 10 SEO tips to make yor site better for Google.</p>
        <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-4">
          <li>
            Start by doing keyword research to understand which terms and
            phrases are most relevant and valuable to your business and target
            audience.
          </li>
          <li>
            Make sure your website is mobile-friendly and has a fast loading
            speed, as these are important factors in search engine rankings.
          </li>
          <li>
            Use a clear and concise URL structure to help search engines
            understand the hierarchy and structure of your website.
          </li>
          <li>
            Use headings and subheadings to break up your content and make it
            more easily accessible to both users and search engines.
          </li>
          <li>
            Optimize your website's images and videos by including relevant
            keywords in their file names and captions.
          </li>
          <li>
            Use internal linking to help search engines understand the
            relationship between your pages and how they are all connected.
          </li>
          <li>
            Regularly updat your website with fresh, high-quality content to
            keep users engaged and show search engines that your site is active
            and valuable.
          </li>
          <li>
            Monitor your website's performance and track your rankings for
            relevant keywords to see how well your SEO efforts are paying off.
          </li>
          <li>
            Consider using social media to promote your website and drive
            traffic to it, as search engines may use social signals as a ranking
            factor.
          </li>
          <li>
            Above all, make sure your website provides a good user experience
            and offers valuable, informative content that people will want to
            share and link to.
          </li>
        </ol>
      </div>
      <!-- Pannel -->
      <div
        class="relative mt-12 bg-neutral-700 rounded-full flex justify-between items-center"
      >
        <div
          class="bg-transparent focus:outline-none min-w-full rounded-full px-6 py-4"
        >
          <div class="text-neutral-200 font-normal">Write me 10 SEO tips</div>
        </div>
        <div class="absolute right-6">
          <AIPointer />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
